LLM_response:
To select all document text in the LibreOffice Writer application shown on the screen, the most reliable method would be to use a keyboard shortcut. The shortcut for selecting all text in a document is typically "Ctrl+A". Assuming the active window is the document in LibreOffice Writer, the following JSON formatted action would accomplish this subtask:

```json
[
    {"action_type":"KeyboardAction","keyboard_action_type":"press","keyboard_key":"Ctrl+A"}
]
```

